</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-28_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-0103aed1-d087-4edc-bf62-0fc4e6d94d6d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Understanding and acknowledging our worth stands as a pillar of individual growth and resilience in the intricate web of human interactions. The importance of valuing oneself cannot be overstated, whether in personal realms where our relationships and mental well-being are centred or in professional settings where our career trajectories and job satisfaction take the stage.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-200_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-20551912-2703-4fe3-b884-3eb8aa8d4fb6"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In this blog, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">Dr Richard Dune</span></em></a> delves into the significance of self-worth in both these arenas while highlighting potential drawbacks if misinterpreted or taken to extremes.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-33_">Key definitions
</h3><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-dcbf620f-c4e6-494d-ad29-e90c7a6f467d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Here are some key definitions used in this article:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-38_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-39_"><strong>Self-worth</strong> - A sense of one's value or worth as a person. It's a fundamental belief about the intrinsic value one possesses, regardless of external circumstances or opinions.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-41_"><strong>Narcissism</strong> - Excessive interest in or admiration of oneself and one's physical appearance. It can also imply a personality trait where individuals seek excessive admiration and attention and lack empathy for others.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-43_"><strong>Boundaries</strong> - Individuals set limits to define safe treatments and interactions with others. In personal relationships, boundaries refer to emotional, physical, and mental limits we establish to protect ourselves.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-45_"><strong>Overconfidence</strong> - An inflated confidence in one's skills, knowledge, or judgment. Overconfidence can lead individuals to underestimate potential risks or overestimate their abilities.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-47_"><strong>Self-awareness</strong> - Conscious knowledge of one's character, feelings, motives, and desires. It's the ability to see oneself clearly and objectively through introspection and reflection.
</li></ul><p class="sc-bhqpXc fHzOVK pf-49_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-72966087-8dfd-4b56-a438-95a1b78a3502"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Each of these terms plays a pivotal role in understanding the depth and nuances of valuing oneself in varied settings.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-52_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-53_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-54_">Valuing oneself in personal settings
